==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catachrestical
<hw>Cat`a*chres"tic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Belonging to, or in the manner of, a catachresis; constituting,
characterized by or given to catachresis; wrested from its natural sense
or form; forced; far-fetched.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Cat`a*chres"tic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A] <qex>catachrestical</qex> and improper way of speaking.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cataclasm</ent>⟦br⟧
